ZH: 他受到了歧视。
EN: He was discriminated against.

ZH: 不应该因为种族差异来歧视别人。
EN: People should not be discriminated against because of their race.

ZH: 这是种族歧视的行为。
EN: This is an act of racial discrimination.

ZH: 在这个社会中，仍然存在着性别歧视。
EN: Gender discrimination still exists in this society.

ZH: 我们应该反对任何形式的歧视。
EN: We should oppose all forms of discrimination.

ZH: 这种歧视行为是不可接受的。
EN: This discriminatory behavior is unacceptable.

ZH: 宗教歧视是严重违背人权的。
EN: Religious discrimination is a serious violation of human rights.

ZH: 他因为外貌不符合标准而遭受了歧视。
EN: He was discriminated against because his appearance didn't meet the standards.

ZH: 歧视是一种严重的社会问题。
EN: Discrimination is a serious social issue.

ZH: 我们应该努力消除一切形式的歧视。
EN: We should strive to eliminate all forms of discrimination.

ZH: 他在工作中经常被歧视。
EN: He is often discriminated against at work.

ZH: 歧视对一个人的心理健康有害。
EN: Discrimination is harmful to a person's mental health.

ZH: 我们应该尽力保护受到歧视的人。
EN: We should do our best to protect those who are discriminated against.

ZH: 歧视是对人格的侮辱。
EN: Discrimination is an insult to one's dignity.

ZH: 社会应该创造一个没有歧视的环境。
EN: Society should create an environment free from discrimination.

ZH: 每个人都有权利不受歧视。
EN: Everyone has the right not to be discriminated against.

ZH: 年龄歧视是十分普遍的现象。
EN: Age discrimination is a very common phenomenon.

ZH: 思想的歧视会限制一个人的发展。
EN: Discrimination based on beliefs can restrict a person's development.

ZH: 我们应该教育人们尊重每个人，不容忍歧视。
EN: We should educate people to respect everyone and not tolerate discrimination.

ZH: 歧视是社会和平的威胁。
EN: Discrimination is a threat to social harmony.
